.TH "devm_register_netdev" 9 "devm_register_netdev" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_register_netdev \- resource managed variant of register_netdev()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_register_netdev
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct net_device *ndev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
managing device for this netdev - usually the parent device
.IP "ndev" 12
device to register

This is a devres variant of \fBregister_netdev\fP for which the unregister
function will be call automatically when the managing device is
detached. Note: the net_device used must also be resource managed by
the same struct device.
